MATCH (ah:AccountHolder)-[:HAS_BANKACCOUNT]->(ba:BankAccount) 
WHERE ba.balance > 7000
MATCH (ah)-[:HAS_CREDITCARD]->(cc:CreditCard)
WHERE cc.limit > 50000
RETURN ah.fullName

NL Question: Retrieve the names of FinancialInstitutes that have at least two BankAccounts with balances exceeding 8000, and list the account numbers associated with those accounts.
Cypher:
MATCH (fi:FinancialInstitute)<-[:FROM]-(ba:BankAccount)
WHERE ba.balance > 8000
WITH fi, COLLECT(ba.accountNumber) AS accountNumbers, count(ba) AS accountCount
WHERE accountCount >= 2
RETURN fi.name, accountNumbers

NL Question: Find the AccountHolders who have made purchases from shops with the business type 'expedite compelling paradigms' and have a credit card with late payments greater than 0. Return the full name of the AccountHolder and the amount of the purchase.
Cypher:
MATCH (ah:AccountHolder)-[:HAS_CREDITCARD]->(cc:CreditCard)
WHERE cc.latePayments > 0
MATCH (p:Purchase)-[:WITH_LOGIN]->(l:Login)-[:FOR_SHOP]->(s:Shop)
WHERE s.business = 'expedite compelling paradigms'
MATCH (p)-[:WITH_CARD]->(card:BankCard)
WITH ah, p
RETURN ah.fullName, p.amount
